    <svcsection id="s16014" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5069" date="06/04/1996">
        <title>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>2000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <title>SYSTEM</title>
                    <para>This section includes information on HFC-134A refrigerant.</para>
                    <para>The Air Conditioning-Heater unit and Heater (only) System are of different construction. The
                        blower and core units of each system mount inside the cab on the lower dash panel of the
                        passenger side (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601401">Figure 1</hotlnk>,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601402">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk document="s16014_3.xml" xrefid="f1601405">Figure 5</hotlnk>). The units are hidden from
                        view by trim panels just below the instrument panel.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601401" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601401" filename="../figg16/g1601401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="514px" scalefitheight="392px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Blend-Air System</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. MAGNETIC CLUTCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. SHUTTER OVERRIDE PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CONDENSER</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. RECEIVER-DEHYDRATOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. REFRIGERANT HOSES</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. HEATER HOSES</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. INTAKE AIR BOX</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. HIGH-SPEED RELAY</callout1>
                            <callout1>10. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                            <callout1>11. REGISTER</callout1>
                            <callout1>12. BLOWER MOTOR AND WHEEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>13. AIR FILTER</callout1>
                            <callout1>14. THERMOSTAT SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>15. BLEND-AIR DOOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>16. WATER VALVE</callout1>
                            <callout1>17. EVAPORATOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>18. EXPANSION VALVE</callout1>
                            <callout1>19. LOW/HIGH PRESSURE RELAY</callout1>
                            <callout1>20. BLOWER RESISTOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>21. CONTROL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>22. FLOOR HEAT DUMP</callout1>
                            <callout1>23. FLOOR HEAT DUMP CONTROL</callout1>
                            <callout1>24. SOLENOID VALVES</callout1>
                            <callout1>25. FAN OVERRIDE SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>26. PRESSURE RELIEF VALVE (HFC-134A)</callout1>
                            <callout1>27. HIGH PRESSURE SAFETY SWITCH (HFC-134A)</callout1>
                            <callout1>28. LOW PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f1601402" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601402" filename="../figg16/g1601402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2. Blend-Air Unit, Installed with Cover Removed</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>Effective January 1, 1993 for 2000, 4000 and 8000 models, the air conditioning systems
                                will be charged with HFC-134A refrigerant. Refer to GROUP 16, CTS-5062, AIR CONDITIONING
                                BASIC THEORY, SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS AND SERVICE section in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual
                                for precautions and changes in service procedures and tools to use with HFC-134A
                                refrigerant.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>COMBINED AIR CONDITIONING/HEATER</title>
                    <para>The Blend-Air air conditioning and heating system is a combination unit (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601401">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Both the heater and air conditioner are housed in
                        one unit and use common ducts and blowers. The term "Blend-Air" refers to the mixing or blending
                        together of air from the cooling and heating systems. The unit provides for heating, cooling,
                        defrosting, dehumidification, and ventilation in any combination the driver chooses.
                    </para>
                    <para>All components of the system may be serviced without removing the unit. The heater, evaporator
                        core and blowers are located in an enclosure behind the instrument panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601403">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601403" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601403" filename="../figg16/g1601403.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="392px" scalefitheight="472px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3. Blend-Air Unit Components</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. BLOWER MOTOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. EVAPORATOR CORE</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. BLEND-AIR DOOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. THERMOSTATIC TEMPERATURE CONTROL SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. HOT WATER FLOW CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. EXPANSION VALVE</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. LOW PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. BLOWER RESISTOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>10. HIGH PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
